race.comment: WING NUT (4) is ticking along nicely of late, following up back-to-back wins with two minor placings. Is drawn to get the gun run and gets in well again with the claim. Can add another win to the tally. TALKACHINO (3) made light work of his rivals last time at Tamworth and can keep the ball rolling here with JPH sticking. Major threat. TILLMAN (11) doesn't win out of turn but boasts peaks that measure up. Will appreciate reuniting with hot-hand hoop in Boudvillain, who has scored aboard prior. Draws well and can play a major role. MISSY MOSS (6) settled well back last time out then found the line strongly to finish fourth over 1400m at Tamworth. Should appreciate the rise to the mile and is one of the main contenders.
